<MudContainer MaxWidth="@MaxWidth.Large">
    <CHPostHeader PostInfo="@PostInfo" />
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Disclaimer!
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Continue supporting local arcades! A home DDR setup should mainly be used for special practice.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Also, any download links may be taken off of this page in the future. These are pretty much just raw notes I documented for myself while doing the setup.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Note: These notes assume you're running Windows.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        How To Get The Game Running
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Get the DanceDanceRevolution A20 PLUS dumped game files. Download link: <MudLink Href="https://nyaa.si/view/1509737" Target="_blank">https://nyaa.si/view/1509737</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Open the magnet file with your BitTorrent client of choice (I use Tixati) and start the download.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Download spice2x from <MudLink Href="https://github.com/spice2x/spice2x.github.io/releases" Target="_blank">https://github.com/spice2x/spice2x.github.io/releases</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="3." />Configure spice2x.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Note: The following steps are roughly copied from <MudLink Href="https://two-torial.xyz/games/ddrace/setup" Target="_blank">https://two-torial.xyz/games/ddrace/setup</MudLink> and <MudLink Href="https://nyaa.si/view/1509737" Target="_blank">https://nyaa.si/view/1509737</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Copy "spice.exe" (the non-64-bit version!) and "spicecfg.exe" to the "contents" directory of the game.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Run spicecfg.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Go to the "Options" tab.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Enable "Basic Local EA Emulation".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Assign "PCBID" to <CHCodeInline>00010203040506070809</CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="3" /><CHTextBullet />Idk what this does but it's a code I copied from that nyaa.si page.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="4." />Attempt to run the game by starting "spice.exe".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />You will likely crash from an access violation after the log "M:ddr: Renderer:initGs() end."
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />If so, you need to install Direct X. Download link: <MudLink Href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=35" Target="_blank">https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=35</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="5." />Download and install a K-Lite Codec Pack from <MudLink Href="https://codecguide.com/download_kl.htm" Target="_blank">https://codecguide.com/download_kl.htm</MudLink>. This is for the game to be able to play the music videos.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />I got the "Standard" pack so I can also have fun looking at the game files but you only need the "Basic" pack for the videos to work in-game.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Extra Steps
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Tip: Spice's "Coin Mech" button doesn't seem to do anything to the credits/coins in-game. You can use the "Service" input instead to add coins.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        How to enable English (or other languages) by default.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Open the game's test menu (via the "Test" input).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Enter "GAME OPTIONS".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="3." />Assign "LANGUAGE SETTING" to "English".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Use "Service" input to sift through the choices.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        You might be interested in setting a few other options as well in the test menu. E.g., required coins per credit.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Note: The base game version for A20 PLUS is <CHCodeInline>2022020200</CHCodeInline>. Updates can be applied from there if you want A3 or beyond.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Using Patches (And Tweaking Latency!)
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Patches are like "cheats". They are similar to Gecko codes for the Wii/GameCube.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Note: Steps copied from <MudLink Href="https://two-torial.xyz/extras/patchsp2x" Target="_blank">https://two-torial.xyz/extras/patchsp2x</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Open your game's spicecfg and go to the "Patches" tab.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Enable "Auto apply patches on game start" (unless you want to permanently modify the game files for some reason).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="3." />Hit "Import from URL" and enter <MudLink Href="https://sp2x.two-torial.xyz/" Target="_blank">https://sp2x.two-torial.xyz/</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="4." />Enable the desired patches.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Patches I use:
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"Song Unlock"
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"Unlock options"
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"SSQ Offset" or a combination of "Render Offset" and "Sound Offset".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Set these offsets to the latency of your TV and/or speakers.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Applying Updates
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Download link: <MudLink Href="https://pixeldrain.com/l/5qZrnRd1" Target="_blank">https://pixeldrain.com/l/5qZrnRd1</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        An "update" is just a file structure of the game which contains only the files that differ from the previous version of the game and any new files as well.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        "Applying" an update just means adding and replacing your game files with the update's files. Make sure you apply these updates in order.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        The next time you open the game you'll get a new Windows firewall pop-up. After accepting, you'll get a warning log and the game will be frozen on startup. Just restart the game and it will work the next time now that the firewall is configured.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Additional Notes
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        The 1cc Discord server has a lot of good info and download links. Invite link: <MudLink Href="https://discord.gg/e7xffWFf9p" Target="_blank">https://discord.gg/e7xffWFf9p</MudLink>. This server seems to be the revival of an original "1cc" Discord community.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Random note: Convenient window position for a fullscreen-like experience at 1920x1080: <CHCodeInline>-8,-31</CHCodeInline>. Double these offsets if your running 4k (3840x2160).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Helpful for testing the game while being able to alt-tab out and back in.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />The game seems to break if window focus is taken away during fullscreen.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />It's definitely worth using fullscreen though when you actually want to play! Runs way faster.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        My current choice for key bindings:
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P1 menu arrows: WASD.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P1 start: Left shift.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P2 menu arrows: Arrow keys.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P2 start: Right shift.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Test menu: Backtick key (the "tilde" key).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Insert coin: Insert key.
    </MudText>
</MudContainer>

